cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is focused on language modelling and improving the learning of long-range dependency of sequence data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel regularizer to improve the learning of long-range dependency. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to maximize the mutual information of sequence variables. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of a regularizer to improve the performance of a neural network model. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of a regularizer to improve the generation quality of language models, which could be relevant to natural language processing tasks in computer vision.
